
install client ubuntu server
add desktop: sudo apt-get install ubuntu-desktop
add chromium:  "add software"


install server ubuntu server
apt update
add npm

create web folder and go to it
npm init
install express with:  npm install express --save

create the entry point file / index.js if left default with the following 4 lines:

const express = require('express')
const app = express()
app.get('/', (req, res) => res.send('Hello World!'))
app.listen(80, () => console.log('Example app listening on port 80!'))

RUN web service with:
node index.js   |  note this assumes walking through:  https://gist.github.com/isaacs/579814
or will have to sudo node index.js  which is an extremely bad setup  unless you want the server hacked 
